VALUES
(40, 23, 31, 6, 24, 22, 22, NULL, 'Witnesses Against Themselves', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of being witnesses against themselves. In Matthew, the people acknowledge their lineage to those who killed prophets, while in Joshua, they affirm their choice to serve the Lord as witnesses.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 23, 31, 18, 15, 5, 6, 'ye be witnesses unto yourselves', 'Condemnation by One''s Own Words', 'Both passages emphasize the idea that individuals are held accountable for their own actions and words. In Matthew, the witnesses condemn themselves as children of those who killed the prophets, while in Job, one''s own mouth testifies against them.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 23, 31, 42, 19, 22, 22, 'children of them which killed the prophets', 'Judgment of the Wicked', 'This connection highlights the theme of judgment against those who reject God''s messengers. Both passages emphasize accountability for one''s actions, with Matthew referencing the children of those who killed prophets and Luke illustrating judgment based on the servant''s knowledge of the master''s expectations.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 23, 31, 19, 64, 8, 8, 'witnesses unto yourselves', 'Witnesses and Self-Destruction', 'This connection highlights the theme of self-incrimination. Both passages emphasize how individuals bear witness to their own actions, leading to their downfall.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 23, 32, 1, 15, 16, 16, 'fill ye up', 'Connection of Iniquity and Fulfillment', 'This connection highlights the theme of filling up iniquity. Both passages emphasize the completion of wrongdoing, as seen in ''fill ye up'' and ''iniquity... not yet full.''', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 23, 32, 4, 32, 14, 14, 'fill ye up then the measure', 'Connection of Sinful Legacy', 'Both passages emphasize the continuation of sinful behavior across generations. Matthew 23:32''s call to ''fill ye up'' reflects a similar idea in Numbers 32:14, where the new generation is described as ''an increase of sinful men.''', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 23, 32, 52, 2, 16, 16, 'fill ye up then the measure', 'Connection of Sin and Judgment', 'Both passages emphasize the idea of ''filling up'' in relation to sin and judgment. In Matthew, it refers to the actions of the fathers, while in 1 Thessalonians, it pertains to the sins of those forbidding salvation to the Gentiles.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 23, 32, 38, 5, 6, 11, 'fill ye up then the measure', 'Wickedness and Judgment Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of filling up the measure of wickedness, as seen in Matthew''s call to complete the sins of the fathers, paralleling Zechariah''s depiction of wickedness personified in the ephah. Both passages emphasize the culmination of iniquity leading to divine judgment.', 'theme', 0.3, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 23, 33, 40, 3, 7, 7, 'ye generation of vipers', 'Generation of Vipers Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the phrase ''generation of vipers'' to describe the Pharisees and Sadducees. This connection highlights a shared condemnation of their actions and a warning of impending judgment.', 'keyword', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 23, 33, 40, 12, 34, 34, 'ye generation of vipers', 'Connection of Viper Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize the phrase ''generation of vipers,'' highlighting the evil nature of the audience. This connection underscores the theme of hypocrisy and the consequences of their words and actions.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 23, 33, 42, 3, 7, 7, 'ye generation of vipers', 'Connection of Viper Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize the phrase ''generation of vipers,'' highlighting a shared condemnation of the people addressed. This connection underscores a warning about impending judgment and the need for repentance.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 23, 33, 43, 8, 44, 44, 'ye serpents, ye generation of vipers', 'Connection of Serpents and Lies', 'Both passages emphasize deceit and evil. In Matthew, the term ''serpents'' suggests cunning, while John identifies the devil as a liar, linking both to malevolent behavior.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 23, 33, 1, 3, 15, 15, 'ye serpents, ye generation of vipers', 'Connection of Serpents and Enmity', 'This connection highlights the theme of enmity between serpents and humanity. Both passages emphasize the conflict between evil, represented by serpents, and the righteous, suggesting a struggle against sin and its consequences.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 23, 33, 19, 58, 3, 5, 'ye serpents', 'Connection of Serpent Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of wickedness associated with serpents. In Matthew, the phrase ''ye serpents'' directly connects to the ''poison of a serpent'' in Psalms, illustrating the deceitful nature of the wicked.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 23, 33, 66, 12, 9, 9, 'ye serpents, ye generation of vipers', 'Connection of Serpent Imagery', 'This connection highlights the use of ''serpent'' to represent evil and deception in both passages. In Matthew, the term is directed at the Pharisees, while in Revelation, it refers to the Devil, linking both to the theme of spiritual corruption.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 23, 34, 40, 10, 16, 17, NULL, 'Persecution of Prophets and Disciples', 'Both passages emphasize the persecution faced by those sent by God. They highlight the violence and opposition that prophets and disciples will encounter, including being scourged in synagogues.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 23, 34, 40, 13, 52, 52, 'scribes', 'Connection of Scribes and Persecution', 'Both passages emphasize the role of scribes in relation to the kingdom of heaven and the persecution they face. The mention of ''scribes'' in both contexts highlights their significance in the teachings of Jesus and the challenges they endure.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 23, 34, 51, 1, 28, 28, 'wise men, and scribes', 'Connection of Teaching and Persecution', 'Both passages emphasize the role of teaching and warning. Matthew speaks of prophets being sent, while Colossians highlights preaching and teaching every man.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 23, 34, 42, 11, 49, 51, 'I send unto you prophets', 'Connection of Prophets and Persecution', 'Both passages emphasize the sending of prophets and their persecution. They highlight the violent response of the generation to God''s messengers, linking the bloodshed of prophets throughout history to the current generation''s actions.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 23, 34, 44, 13, 1, 1, 'prophets', 'Connection of Prophets and Persecution', 'This connection highlights the presence of prophets in both passages. In Matthew, Jesus speaks of sending prophets who will face persecution, while Acts mentions prophets in the church at Antioch, suggesting a continuity of prophetic ministry amidst challenges.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 23, 34, 14, 36, 15, 16, 'prophets, and wise men, and scribes', 'Connection of Prophets and Persecution', 'Both passages emphasize the sending of prophets and the persecution they face. Matthew 23:34 mentions the killing and scourging of prophets, while 2 Chronicles 36:15-16 describes how messengers were mocked and misused.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 23, 34, 20, 11, 30, 30, 'wise men, and scribes', 'Wisdom and Righteousness Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of wisdom in both passages. Matthew discusses the persecution of wise individuals, while Proverbs emphasizes the value of winning souls as a sign of wisdom.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 23, 35, 14, 24, 20, 22, 'the blood of Zacharias son of Barachias', 'Connection of Righteous Bloodshed', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of righteous bloodshed, with Matthew referencing the murder of Zechariah, who is stoned in 2 Chronicles. This connection highlights the continuity of violence against God''s messengers throughout biblical history.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 23, 35, 38, 1, 1, 1, 'righteous blood shed upon the earth', 'Connection of Righteous Blood', 'This connection highlights the theme of righteous bloodshed, linking Abel''s murder to the death of Zechariah. Both passages emphasize the consequences of violence against the righteous.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 23, 35, 58, 11, 4, 4, 'righteous blood shed upon the earth', 'Connection of Righteous Blood', 'This connection highlights the theme of righteous bloodshed, linking Abel''s sacrifice to the condemnation of those who kill the righteous. Both passages emphasize the significance of Abel''s righteousness and the consequences of violence against the innocent.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 23, 35, 1, 4, 8, 8, 'righteous blood shed upon the earth', 'Connection of Righteous Bloodshed', 'This connection highlights the theme of righteous bloodshed, linking Abel''s murder by Cain to the broader context of violence against the righteous. Both passages emphasize the consequences of such acts, culminating in the judgment mentioned in Matthew.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 23, 35, 66, 18, 24, 24, NULL, 'Connection of Righteous Blood', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of bloodshed, specifically the blood of the righteous and prophets. Matthew references the blood of Abel and Zacharias, while Revelation speaks of the blood of prophets and saints, linking them through the idea of those slain upon the earth.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 23, 35, 12, 21, 16, 16, 'righteous blood shed upon the earth', 'Connection of Innocent Bloodshed', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of innocent bloodshed, with Matthew referencing the blood of Abel and Zacharias, while 2 Kings highlights Manasseh''s actions in Jerusalem. This connection highlights the consequences of violence against the righteous.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 23, 35, 12, 24, 4, 4, NULL, 'Connection of Innocent Blood', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of innocent bloodshed. Matthew references the blood of Abel and Zacharias, while 2 Kings speaks of innocent blood in Jerusalem, highlighting the severity of violence against the righteous.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 23, 36, 40, 10, 23, 23, 'verily I say unto you', 'Connection of Generational Judgment', 'Both passages emphasize the urgency of the present generation''s response to Jesus. The phrase ''verily I say unto you'' in both verses underscores the seriousness of His message regarding impending events.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
